56 Paladin of Tunare- Vallis Scortor
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usanterre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santerre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/13/02 6:49:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1490.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OK</span><hr size=1> Buzcam, Gulor - I agree in principle.  I don't want the government to have unlimited powers to arrest citizens and hold them without charging them indefinitely.  <br>
<br>
But look at the other side of the coin, as a citizen, or as the administration.  What happens if you are watching this guy, you know he's met with Al Queda, you have *circumstantial* evidence that he is planning to set off a dirty bomb... and you lose him... and he blows it off in Times Square on New Year's Eve, irradiating a million people?  If I were Mr. Ashcroft, I'd rather have some folks crying foul about me violating some scumbag's civil rights then have all that blood on my hands.  <br>
<br>
Sometimes life gives you hard choices, and dogmatically following the rules without regard for common sense is not your best option.  If I knew for certain someone was going to go into a kindergarten class and open fire, I'd most certainly kill them first even if it meant I would spend the rest of my life in jail.<br>
<br>
Something else to think about - perhaps he is being kept from communicating with his lawyer because the nuclear material is still at large, and they don't want the lawyer sending info to his cronies on its whereabouts.  Perhaps, once secured, they will be able to release more info and try him as a citizen?  To me, that is justifiable, but we'll have to see it play out. <p><BR><br><B><I><img src="http://www.druidmail.com/santerre2.gif">Santerre.</I></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugulorgularin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gulor Gularin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/13/02 6:58:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1490.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OK</span><hr size=1> Santerre wrote-<br>
